<div id="review_2433843666" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2433843666" />
    <a title="Jason Koivu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1742824-jason-koivu"><img alt="Jason Koivu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1560521450p2/1742824.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2433843666?book_show_action=true">Jun 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jason Koivu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jason Koivu" href="/user/show/1742824-jason-koivu">Jason Koivu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1742824-jason-koivu?shelf=detective">detective</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1742824-jason-koivu?shelf=crime">crime</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1742824-jason-koivu?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2433843666" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6247083559493564594">I don&apos;t think I appreciate Dorothy Sayers as much as I should. Really, this is probably a 4-star book that I&apos;ve given only 3, because I felt she got away from the murder solving a bit too much. I should be enjoying her long asides into the advertising world and the game of cricket. I should be impressed by the seriousness in which she handles drugs and death. It&apos;s all quite masterful and ahead of her time. I mean to say, her craft and characters are more mature than her contemporaries. Perhaps I</span>
  <span id="freeText6247083559493564594" style="display:none">I don't think I appreciate Dorothy Sayers as much as I should. Really, this is probably a 4-star book that I've given only 3, because I felt she got away from the murder solving a bit too much. I should be enjoying her long asides into the advertising world and the game of cricket. I should be impressed by the seriousness in which she handles drugs and death. It's all quite masterful and ahead of her time. I mean to say, her craft and characters are more mature than her contemporaries. Perhaps I've been too inured by the short, punchy detective fiction of many other authors of the genre. Honestly, <i>Murder Must Advertise</i> is truly a good read. I'm not sure I'm a deserving reader though.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6247083559493564594" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


