<span id="freeTextContainer17396214037051901267">Re-read. I think I enjoyed this even more this time around knowing DL Sayers worked in an advertising office. The whole Whiffling subplot follows Sayers own advertising experience closely with the famous “mustard” campaign which is also mentioned in this book. </span>

          </span>
