<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer10038089827898055676">Dorothy Leigh Sayers was a renowned British author, translator, student of classical and modern languages, and Christian humanist.<br/><br/>Dorothy L. Sayers is best known for her mysteries, a series of novels and short stories set between World War I and World War II that feature English aristocrat and amateur sleuth Lord Peter Wimsey. However, Sayers herself considered her translation of Dante&apos;s Divina Co</span>
  <span id="freeText10038089827898055676" style="display:none">Dorothy Leigh Sayers was a renowned British author, translator, student of classical and modern languages, and Christian humanist.<br /><br />Dorothy L. Sayers is best known for her mysteries, a series of novels and short stories set between World War I and World War II that feature English aristocrat and amateur sleuth Lord Peter Wimsey. However, Sayers herself considered her translation of Dante's Divina Commedia to be her best work. She is also known for her plays and essays.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10038089827898055676" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

